NodeJS:
------

    - NodeJS is the server side scripting language.

    - By using NodeJS, we can create http&tcp servers.

    - In general we can develop Node Applications by using JavaScript.

    - Node will support both predefined and user defined modules.


Modules in NodeJS
-----------------
1.express
    - this module used to develop the REST API.

2.mysql
    - this module used to interact with the mysql database.

3.mongodb
     - this module used to interact with the mongo database.

4. body-parser
      - this module used to set the MIME Type.

Ex.
        JSON
        Text
        XML
        --
        --
        --

5. fs
      - this module used to interact with the flat files.

6. jwt-simple
        - this module used to maintain the token based authentication system.

7. http
        - this module used to develop the http servers.

8. query-string
        - this module used to prepare the ORM Queries.


----------------------------------------

in general we can download above modules (custom modules) by using package.json file.

we can execute the package.json file by using following command.

>npm install

[Note : when ever we execute npm install , automatically modules will be downloads to node_modules folder].



Ex_1:
    Basic Communication Between AngularJS to NodeJS
    -----------------------------------------------


Step 1:
        download express module.


Step 2:
        prepare the angular application.

        Ex.
            index.html

Step 3:
        prepare the node application

        Ex.
            server.js



Step 4:
    start the server

> npm start


Step 5:
    launch the application with the browser

    http://localhost:8080/


